      "bodyHtml": "<div class='max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8'><div class='card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border-l-4 border-primary'><div class='card-body'><h1 class='card-title text-2xl font-bold leading-snug'>The central role of knowledge integration capability in service innovation-based competitive strategy</h1><div class='flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2'><span class='badge badge-primary badge-outline'>Industrial Marketing Management</span><span class='badge badge-secondary badge-outline'>Vol. 76 (2019), pp. 144-156</span><span class='badge badge-accent badge-outline'>quantitative</span></div><p class='mt-2 text-base-content/70'>저자: Sandeep Salunke</p><p class='text-xs text-base-content/50'>DOI: 10.1016/j.indmarman.2018.07.004</p></div></div><div class='card bg-base-100 shadow'><div class='card-body'><h2 class='card-title border-l-4 border-accent pl-3 text-xl mb-4'>STEP 1 — 초록 번역</h2><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6'><div><p class='text-sm font-semibold text-base-content/60 mb-2'>영문 원문</p><blockquote class='border-l-4 border-base-300 pl-4 italic text-sm text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed'>This study examines how B2B service firms organize and manage knowledge in order to deliver new value adding solutions and in turn competitive advantage, addressing calls for research into this important, yet neglected area. Speci fically, this study: (1) examines the role of the antecedents of knowledge integration capability (KIC) in service innovation-led competitive advantage in project-oriented B2B service firms; and (2) models and empirically tests the links between KIC and service innovation, and in turn sustainable competitive advantage (SCA). Findings from our research of Australian and US project-oriented firms support our central theorization that the new knowledge acquired through external and internal sources per se is not suﬃcient, but should be integrated with existing knowledge in order to deliver innovative service solutions addressing clients&#x27; needs. Results from testing non-linear eff ects of new knowledge con figurations on service innovation provide deeper insights into the suggested relationship. Our research contributes to calls for comprehensive frameworks of service innovation-led competitive advantage. We provide theoretical and managerial implications, and suggest areas for future research.</blockquote></div><div><p class='text-sm font-semibold text-base-content/60 mb-2'>한국어 번역</p><blockquote class='border-l-4 border-primary/40 pl-4 text-sm text-base-content leading-relaxed'>외부·내부 지식을 통합하는 역량이 서비스 혁신과 지속가능 경쟁우위를 만든다. 지식의 양보다 통합이 핵심이다.</blockquote></div></div></div></div><div class='card bg-base-100 shadow'><div class='card-body'><h2 class='card-title border-l-4 border-accent pl-3 text-xl mb-4'>STEP 2 — 핵심 주장 (1분 설명용)</h2><div class='alert alert-success mb-6'><span class='font-bold'>한 줄 요약:</span><span class='ml-2'>외부·내부 지식을 통합하는 역량이 서비스 혁신과 지속가능 경쟁우위를 만든다. 지식의 양보다 통합이 핵심이다.</span></div><ul class='steps steps-vertical'><li class='step step-primary'><div class='text-left ml-4'><p class='font-semibold'>연구 질문</p><p class='text-sm text-base-content/70'>This study examines how B2B service firms organize and manage knowledge in order to deliver new value adding solutions and in turn competitive advantage, addressing calls for research into this important, yet neglected area.</p></div></li><li class='step step-primary'><div class='text-left ml-4'><p class='font-semibold'>핵심 발견</p><p class='text-sm text-base-content/70'>We provide theoretical and managerial implications, and suggest areas for future research.</p></div></li><li class='step step-primary'><div class='text-left ml-4'><p class='font-semibold'>이론적·실무적 기여</p><p class='text-sm text-base-content/70'>외부·내부 지식을 통합하는 역량이 서비스 혁신과 지속가능 경쟁우위를 만든다. 지식의 양보다 통합이 핵심이다.</p></div></li></ul></div></div><div class='card bg-base-100 shadow'><div class='card-body'><h2 class='card-title border-l-4 border-accent pl-3 text-xl mb-4'>STEP 3 — 근거 표</h2><div class='overflow-x-auto'><table class='table table-zebra table-sm w-full'><thead><tr><th>#</th><th>핵심 주장</th><th>근거</th><th>위치</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td class='text-xs italic'>This study examines how B2B service firms organize and manage knowledge in order to deliver new value adding solutions and in turn competitive advantage, addressing calls for research into this important, yet neglected area.</td><td>Abstract</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td class='text-xs italic'>Speci fically, this study: (1) examines the role of the antecedents of knowledge integration capability (KIC) in service innovation-led competitive advantage in project-oriented B2B service firms; and (2) models and empirically tests the links between KIC and service innovation, and in turn sustainable competitive advantage (SCA).</td><td>Abstract</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td class='text-xs italic'>Findings from our research of Australian and US project-oriented firms support our central theorization that the new knowledge acquired through external and internal sources per se is not suﬃcient, but should be integrated with existing knowledge in order to deliver innovative service solutions addressing clients&#x27; needs.</td><td>Abstract</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div><div class='card bg-base-100 shadow'><div class='card-body'><h2 class='card-title border-l-4 border-accent pl-3 text-xl mb-4'>STEP 4 — 연구 방법 분해</h2><ul class='timeline timeline-vertical'><li><div class='timeline-start timeline-box bg-primary text-primary-content'><p class='font-bold'>STEP 1</p><p class='text-xs mt-1'>호주·미국 프로젝트형 B2B 서비스 기업 표본을 대상으로 설문과 비선형/매개 분석을 수행했다.</p></div><div class='timeline-middle'><div class='w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-primary'></div></div><hr class='bg-primary'/></li><li><hr class='bg-secondary'/><div class='timeline-middle'><div class='w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-secondary'></div></div><div class='timeline-end timeline-box bg-secondary text-secondary-content'><p class='font-bold'>STEP 2</p><p class='text-xs mt-1'>핵심 변수·사례·대상을 정리한다.</p></div><hr class='bg-secondary'/></li><li><hr class='bg-accent'/><div class='timeline-middle'><div class='w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-accent'></div></div><div class='timeline-start timeline-box bg-accent text-accent-content'><p class='font-bold'>STEP 3</p><p class='text-xs mt-1'>저자들이 사용한 분석틀/모형을 적용한다.</p></div><hr class='bg-accent'/></li></ul><p class='mt-4 text-sm'><b>재현 가능성 평가:</b> 부분 재현 가능</p></div></div><div class='card bg-base-100 shadow'><div class='card-body'><h2 class='card-title border-l-4 border-accent pl-3 text-xl mb-4'>STEP 5 — Limitation 분리</h2><div class='alert alert-error mb-4'><span class='font-bold'>A. 논문이 스스로 인정한 한계</span><span class='ml-2'>단일 기업·국가 표본에 묶인 일반화 한계</span></div><div class='collapse collapse-arrow bg-warning/10'><input type='checkbox'/><div class='collapse-title font-medium'>B. 논문이 언급하지 않았지만 비판적으로 의심할 점</div><div class='collapse-content'><p>횡단면/관측자료라 역인과와 미관측 교란을 완전히 제거하긴 어렵다.</p></div></div></div></div></div>",
