      "search": "the drivers of success in new-product development robert g. cooper the drivers of success in new-product development the drivers of success in new-product development industrial marketing management vol. 76 (2019), pp. 36-47 review 저자: robert g. cooper doi: 10.1016/j.indmarman.2018.07.005 step 1 — 초록 번역 영문 원문 why are some new products so successful and some companies outstanding performers in new-product development? the article identi fies success factors from numerous research studies into npd (new-product development) performance in industry. three categories of success drivers have been de fined. first, success drivers, that explain the success of individual new-product projects, are more tactical: they capture the characteristics of new product projects, such as certain executional best practices (building in voice-of-customer; doing the front-end homework; and adopting a global orientation for the project), and well as the nature of the product itself (a compelling value proposition, for example). a second category is drivers of success at the business level: they include organizational and strategic factors, such as the business's innovation strategy and how the firm makes its r&d investment decisions; how it organizes for npd; climate and culture; and leadership the third category of success divers identi fied is the systems and methods the firm has in place for managing npd, for example gating systems, agile development approaches, and ideation methods. the details of each of these 20 success drivers, along with their managerial implications, are outlined in the article. 한국어 번역 npd 성공을 프로젝트·사업·시스템의 세 범주로 정리한 리뷰로, 20개 성공요인을 체계화한다. step 2 — 핵심 주장 (1분 설명용) 한 줄 요약: npd 성공을 프로젝트·사업·시스템의 세 범주로 정리한 리뷰로, 20개 성공요인을 체계화한다. 연구 질문 why are some new products so successful and some companies outstanding performers in new-product development? 핵심 발견 the details of each of these 20 success drivers, along with their managerial implications, are outlined in the article. 이론적·실무적 기여 npd 성공을 프로젝트·사업·시스템의 세 범주로 정리한 리뷰로, 20개 성공요인을 체계화한다. step 3 — 근거 표 # 핵심 주장 근거 위치 1 why are some new products so successful and some companies outstanding performers in new-product development? abstract 2 the article identi fies success factors from numerous research studies into npd (new-product development) performance in industry. abstract 3 three categories of success drivers have been de fined. abstract step 4 — 연구 방법 분해 step 1 기존 npd 연구 수십 편을 종합한 리뷰로 성공요인을 분류했다. step 2 핵심 변수·사례·대상을 정리한다. step 3 저자들이 사용한 분석틀/모형을 적용한다. 재현 가능성 평가: 부분 재현 가능 step 5 — limitation 분리 a. 논문이 스스로 인정한 한계 요약·분류 중심이라 원인-결과를 직접 입증하지는 못한다 b. 논문이 언급하지 않았지만 비판적으로 의심할 점 후속 실증 연구가 없으면 처방의 강도가 약하다.",
